Stars like Shane Warne in the past and Shreyas Iyer currently combined tactical acumen with on-field performance. Modern IPL teams focus on players prominent in the playing XI, irrespective of their presence or not in the national T20I team, emphasizing performance and leadership skills.
title: How have IPL franchises evolved for choice of captains

description: The Trump administration released over 31,000 pages of classified documents regarding JFK's assassination, shedding light on key Cold War dynamics, Oswald's movements, and continued intelligence community activities. Most historians believe these documents, though intriguing, won't drastically alter the well-entrenched narratives but will spark intense scrutiny and debate.
title: JFK files unveiled: What they say about assassination

description: Stock market recommendations: Mehul Kothari of Anand Rathi recommends buying BHEL, Astrazeneca Pharma, and Maruti Suzuki India stocks. These picks show favorable breakout patterns suggesting potential price increases.
title: Top stocks to buy today

description: Former U.S. President Donald Trump and Russian President Vladimir Putin recently discussed a potential hockey showdown between NHL and KHL players. However, the NHL distanced itself from the proposal, citing international sanctions on Russian hockey due to geopolitical tensions following Russia's invasion of Ukraine.
title: Trump and Putin discusses potential NHL-KHL Hockey matchup

description: Six Supreme Court judges, including Justice B R Gavai, will visit Manipur to inquire about relief efforts and legal aid in camps amidst ongoing strife. The visit also marks the 20th establishment day of Manipur High Court, which was previously a bench of Gauhati HC.
title: 6 Supreme Court judges to visit restive Manipur this weekend

description: Analysts have maintained 'buy' ratings on pharmaceuticals, steel, and financial stocks, expecting profitable growth. Akums Drugs aims to boost margins, JSW Steel foresees strong demand and price benefits, and Bajaj Finserv's fundamentals remain intact post-split with Allianz. Va Tech Wabag and Baazar Style Retail see robust growth potential.
title: Buy or sell: Stocks on brokerages’ radar for today

description: Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu blamed Hamas for the renewed violence, defending Israel's military operations in Gaza. Netanyahu asserted efforts were made to avoid conflict, but Hamas rejected truce proposals, prompting the offensive. The recent strikes reportedly killed 404 Palestinians and wounded over 560, escalating the conflict further.
title: 'Hamas responsible for this war': Netanyahu after renewed Gaza attacks

description: External affairs minister S Jaishankar criticized the selective application of international rules on sovereignty, citing J&K as an example where an invasion was turned into a dispute. He highlighted the unfair treatment of smaller countries and the inconsistent responses to military regimes in Myanmar and Pakistan, stressing the need for a fairer global order.
title: Longest illegal occupation of territory since WWII in J&K: Jaishankar

description: Taylor Swift takes a break from the limelight after a record-breaking Eras Tour and releases a double album. She spends her time with Travis Kelce, skipping the 2025 iHeartRadio Music Awards, much to fans' disappointment. Swift stays productive, preparing for future projects.
title: Taylor Swift skips iHeartRadio Music Awards, enjoys private time with Travis Kelce

description: Police in Nagpur allegedly used excessive force while searching for riot suspects, damaging property and detaining locals, some of whom claim they were innocent. Residents reported officers breaking doors, smashing vehicles, and arresting people at random during Ramadan. The police recommended that any evidence of misconduct be reported for action.
title: Aftermath of riots: When cops broke down doors, went on rampage in Nagpur

description: A septuagenarian couple was brutally murdered in their Kohat Enclave home in northwest Delhi. Their new caretaker, who was hired just four days prior and is now missing, is the prime suspect. The incident, which appears to be a robbery, has left the community in shock.
title: Gory night in Delhi's Pitampura: Elderly couple strangled, home ransacked

description: Nagpur remains under heightened security with curfew imposed on 30% of the city following violent clashes. Police have fortified sensitive areas and arrested over 50 suspects while 1,200 individuals are accused of involvement. Schools and colleges are shut, and extensive property damage has been reported.
title: Nagpur violence: Officials alarmed by attack’s scale, level of planning

description: A 15-year-old boy attacked Zonal DCP Niketan Kadam with an axe during riots at Hansapuri, aiming for his neck. Kadam blocked the blow with his hand, sustaining serious injuries. He underwent emergency surgery and is currently recovering. The officer and 11 other personnel were injured while trapped by a mob and subsequently rescued by reinforcements.
title: Nagpur violence: 15-year-old attacked IPS Kadam with axe

description: Nagpur Police were unprepared for the intense communal violence erupted in Old Nagpur, leaving 34 policemen injured. The violence spread from Mahal to Hansapuri due to poor intelligence, misjudgment, and inadequate preparation, despite earlier signs of unrest during a right-wing protest and inflammatory video clips.
title: Why Nagpur burned, cops stone-walled?

description: Over 68 lakh cancer treatments under the Ayushman Bharat scheme, valued at over Rs 13,000 crore, have been performed, with 76% in rural areas. 37 specific packages for targeted therapies like chemotherapy are included. Those below the poverty line may receive up to Rs 15 lakh assistance. The government aims to set up 200 daycare cancer centres by 2025-26.
title: Govt: 68 lakh cancer cases treated under PMJAY, 76% of them in rural areas

description: Proposed wage mandates for H-1B visa holders, including a requirement to pay at least the median local wage, may hinder US companies from hiring skilled foreign workers, warns an NFAP study. These mandates could force employers to move jobs offshore, particularly affecting recent graduates in science and engineering, and could weaken the US workforce in key technology sectors.
title: Proposed H-1B wage hike may hurt hiring of freshers, scientists, engineers

description: Sunita Williams, Nasa astronaut, returned to Earth after a nine-month stay on the International Space Station. She arrived with fellow astronauts Butch Wilmore and Nick Hague, and cosmonaut Aleksandr Gorbunov. Williams' mission was extended due to issues with Boeing’s Starliner capsule. She set a record for the most spacewalking time for a female astronaut.
title: Sunita Williams smiles, waves after returning to Earth

description: Sweden's foreign minister, Maria Malmer Stenergard, emphasizes the importance of democracies uniting to uphold a rules-based order in both Ukraine and the Indo-Pacific. Stenergard also discusses Sweden's defence cooperation with India and their commitment to NATO while addressing security concerns related to China and Russia.
title: 'Want fair peace for Ukraine, India has a key role to play': Sweden foreign min

description: BYD has introduced a new electric vehicle (EV) charging technology that can fully charge a car in 5-8 minutes. This breakthrough could challenge Tesla's market position. BYD's new system offers up to 470 kilometers of range in 5 minutes. This innovation highlights the company's commitment to addressing charging time concerns in the EV market.
title: China’s BYD Unveils 5-Minute Tech, Challenging Tesla

description: NASA astronauts like Peggy Whitson, Sunita Williams, and Scott Kelly have set records for the longest space missions on the ISS, contributing significantly to research and exploration. Their extended stays in space have provided invaluable data on the effects of long-duration spaceflight, crucial for future missions to the Moon and Mars.
title: Sunita becomes 2nd astronaut to spend longest time in space – see full list

description: Near Delhi Darwaza in Ahmedabad, a driver in a red Mahindra Thar recklessly evaded police by speeding through a restricted, congested area, narrowly missing an officer. The SUV hit multiple vehicles and caused panic among pedestrians. Police are now searching for the driver, urging the public for any information. This incident highlights increasing cases of reckless driving in the region.
title: Asked to stop, SUV driver tries to run down a cop in Ahmedabad
